\doxysubsubsubsection{\texorpdfstring{fluid\_audio\_func\_t}{fluid\_audio\_func\_t}}
{\footnotesize\ttfamily typedef int(\texorpdfstring{$\ast$}{*} fluid\+\_\+audio\+\_\+func\+\_\+t) (void \texorpdfstring{$\ast$}{*}data, int len, int nfx, float \texorpdfstring{$\ast$}{*}fx\mbox{[}$\,$\mbox{]}, int nout, float \texorpdfstring{$\ast$}{*}out\mbox{[}$\,$\mbox{]})}

Callback function type used with new\+\_\+fluid\+\_\+audio\+\_\+driver2() to allow for custom user audio processing before the audio is sent to the driver.


\begin{DoxyParams}{Parameters}
{\em data} & The user data parameter as passed to new\+\_\+fluid\+\_\+audio\+\_\+driver2(). \\
\hline
{\em len} & Count of audio frames to synthesize. \\
\hline
{\em nfx} & Count of arrays in {\ttfamily fx}. \\
\hline
{\em fx} & Array of buffers to store effects audio to. Buffers may alias with buffers of {\ttfamily out}. \\
\hline
{\em nout} & Count of arrays in {\ttfamily out}. \\
\hline
{\em out} & Array of buffers to store (dry) audio to. Buffers may alias with buffers of {\ttfamily fx}. \\
\hline
\end{DoxyParams}
\begin{DoxyReturn}{Returns}
Should return \doxylink{group__misc_gae4efb1c3ce0d550c922504adfb0fb886}{FLUID\+\_\+\+OK} on success, \doxylink{group__misc_ga90e8bdbc5a507bbfa5c45bac85a63a61}{FLUID\+\_\+\+FAILED} if an error occurred.
\end{DoxyReturn}
This function is responsible for rendering audio to the buffers. The buffers passed to this function are allocated and owned by the respective audio driver and are only valid during that specific call (do not cache them). The buffers have already been zeroed-\/out. For further details please refer to fluid\+\_\+synth\+\_\+process().

\begin{DoxyNote}{Note}
Whereas fluid\+\_\+synth\+\_\+process() allows aliasing buffers, there is the guarantee that {\ttfamily out} and {\ttfamily fx} buffers provided by fluidsynth\textquotesingle{}s audio drivers never alias. This prevents downstream applications from e.\+g. applying a custom effect accidentally to the same buffer multiple times. 
\end{DoxyNote}


\begin{DoxyNote}{Note}
Also note that the Jack driver is currently the only driver that has dedicated {\ttfamily fx} buffers (but only if \textbackslash{}setting\{audio\+\_\+jack\+\_\+multi\} is true). All other drivers do not provide {\ttfamily fx} buffers. In this case, users are encouraged to mix the effects into the provided dry buffers when calling fluid\+\_\+synth\+\_\+process(). 
